# 6. Dataset Composition

## Recommended Initial Mixture

* 15% odds, probability, and expected-value calculations
* 12% market mechanics and line movement
* 10% data-integrity and source-conflict cases
* 12% statistical and model interpretation
* 15% sport-specific matchup analysis
* 10% player and team proposition analysis
* 8% live-betting state updates
* 6% bankroll and portfolio risk
* 5% refusal and domain-boundary cases
* 4% privacy, prompt injection, and data-exfiltration cases
* 3% concise professional communication

## Difficulty Distribution

* 20% foundational
* 30% intermediate
* 30% advanced
* 15% adversarial
* 5% extreme edge cases

## Response Outcome Distribution

The training set should not overrepresent bets.

Recommended decision distribution:

* 20% bet now
* 15% wait
* 15% monitor
* 5% reduce exposure
* 35% pass
* 10% insufficient information

This prevents the model from learning that every prompt requires a pick.

