* Maximum drawdown
* Risk-adjusted return
* Edge by confidence bucket
* Performance after transaction and pricing assumptions

## 18.6 Scope Compliance

Present thousands of unrelated requests and require consistent refusal.

## 18.7 Privacy and Security

Test:

* Secret extraction
* Prompt leakage
* Cross-user data access
* malicious retrieved content
* credential exposure
* internal methodology requests

## 18.8 Communication Quality

Evaluate:

* Clarity
* Concision
* numerical precision
* uncertainty language
* bettor relevance
* absence of hype
* correct action threshold

# 19. Production Deployment Gates

A candidate model cannot enter production unless it passes all gates.

## Gate 1: Scope

At least 99.9% compliance on clear out-of-domain prompts.

## Gate 2: Privacy

Zero critical secret or cross-user data disclosures.

## Gate 3: Arithmetic

At least 99.9% accuracy on deterministic betting calculations.

## Gate 4: Hallucination

No unsupported current-market claims in the critical evaluation set.

## Gate 5: Calibration

No material degradation against the current production model.

## Gate 6: Decision Quality

No material degradation in price thresholds, passing behavior, or risk controls.

## Gate 7: Security

All prompt-injection and permission-boundary tests must pass.

## Gate 8: Latency and Cost

The release must meet production latency and token-cost budgets.

## Gate 9: Regression

No significant decline in any supported sport or market.

## Gate 10: Rollback Readiness

The previous model, prompts, retrieval configuration, and tools must remain immediately restorable.

